On Tue, 6 Aug 2002, Richard Atwell wrote:

> I bought a tester and I'm going to test the compression this weekend.  What
> I know:
>
> - warm up engine first
> - remove all plugs
> - test one by one with throttle wide open each time
>
> What I don't know is the best way to stop the fuel from flowing while I
> perform the test.

Richard,

Use a remote starter switch to crank the engine, not the key.  With the
key off, there is no power to the ECU or fuel pump, thus neither flow nor
spray.  I got this advice from Karl who is (I hope :) asleep, since it is
4 AM in Fresno!

                           Steve Dolan

